### 5. EDHOC and OSCORE Profile
* **Presenter:** Rikard Höglund
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-edhoc-oscore-profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-ace-edhoc-oscore-profile/)
* **Slides:** [EDHOC and OSCORE ACE profile slides IETF 126](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ace-edhoc-and-oscore-ace-profile-slides-ietf-126-00)

#### Discussion:
* Rikard Höglund presented updates in version 11:
  * Clarified prescriptive vs. non-prescriptive parameters in the EDHOC information object.
  * **Reverse Flow Simplification:** Removed the option to place the access token in EDHOC Message 2 (EAD2). It must now only be placed in Message 4 (EAD4). This was done because passive adversary protection in Message 2 requires the AS to always encrypt the token, adding significant operational complexity.
  * Added considerations on the timing of access token requests during reverse flows to ensure proper binding to client credentials.
  * Refined three EAD items: ACE Auth Access Token, credential by value, and request creation hints. The session ID parameter was removed as it is now defined in [draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params/).
  * Added an operational considerations section focusing on RSs belonging to multiple audiences.

