### 6. Group OSCORE Profile
* **Presenter:** Rikard Höglund
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-group-oscore-profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-ace-group-oscore-profile/)
* **Slides:** [IETF 126 ACE Group OSCORE profile slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ace-ietf-126-ace-group-oscore-profile-slides-00)

#### Discussion:
* Rikard Höglund presented the latest changes in version 07:
  * Made proof-of-possession (PoP) evidence from the client optional during access token requests, as the AS may verify this out-of-band.
  * Aligned semantics with the revised `ace_profile` parameter.
  * Simplified how the RS binds the access token to local states. Rather than associating the token with multiple group details, the RS now simply binds it to the Token Series ID, audience, and the client’s authentication credential.
  * Introduced "Token Series" to enable dynamic updates of access rights. A unique Token Series ID is allocated per client-audience pair, allowing the client to easily reference which rights to update.

